- Average population change over three years refers to the mean population change for the current year and the preceding two years; 
- Previous year's population and literacy rates refer to the population and literacy rates of the year immediately preceding the current year; 
- Literacy rate is the percentage of literate individuals within a population; 
- Population growth rate is the rate at which the number of individuals in a population increases; 
- User access sequence and type pertain to the order and manner in which users access demographic and literacy data.
